{"ATRABILARIAN":[{"def":"A person much given to melancholy; a hypochondriac.","pos":""}],"ATRABILIAR":[{"def":"Melancholy; atrabilious.","pos":""}],"ATRABILIARY":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to atra bilis or black bile, a fluid formerly supposed to be produced by the kidneys.","pos":""},{"def":"Melancholic or hypohondriac; atrabilious; -- from the supposed predominance of black bile, to the influence of which the ancients attributed hypochondria, melancholy, and mania.","pos":""}],"ATRABILIOUS":[{"def":"Melancholic or hypochondriac; atrabiliary.","pos":""}],"ATRAMENTACEOUS":[{"def":"Black, like ink; inky; atramental.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to ink; inky; black, like ink; as, atramental galls; atramentous spots.","pos":""}],"ATRAMENTARIOUS":[{"def":"Like ink; suitable for making ink.","pos":""}],"ATREDE":[{"def":"To surpass in council.","pos":""}],"ATRESIA":[{"def":"Absence or closure of a natural passage or channel of the body; imperforation.","pos":""}],"ATRIAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to an atrium.","pos":""}],"ATRIUM":[{"def":"The main part of either auricle of the heart as distinct from the auricular appendix.","pos":""},{"def":"A cavity in ascidians into which the intestine and generative ducts open, and which also receives the water from the gills.","pos":""}],"ATROCHA":[{"def":"A kind of chætopod larva in which no circles of cilia are developed.","pos":""}],"ATROCIOUS":[{"def":"Extremely heinous; full of enormous wickedness; as, atrocious quilt or deeds.","pos":""},{"def":"Characterized by, or expressing, great atrocity, great atrocity.","pos":""}],"ATROCITY":[{"def":"Enormous wickedness; extreme heinousness or cruelty.","pos":""},{"def":"An atrocious or extremely cruel deed.","pos":""}],"ATROPHIC":[{"def":"Relating to atrophy.","pos":""}],"ATROPHIED":[{"def":"Affected with atrophy, as a tissue or organ; arrested in development at a very early stage; rudimentary.","pos":""}],"ATROPHY":[{"def":"A wasting away from want of nourishment; diminution in bulk or slow emaciation of the body or of any part.","pos":""}],"ATROPIA":[{"def":"Same as Atropine.","pos":""}],"ATROPINE":[{"def":"A poisonous, white, crystallizable alkaloid, extracted from the Atropa belladonna, or deadly nightshade, and the Datura Stramonium, or thorn apple.","pos":""}],"ATROPISM":[{"def":"A condition of the system produced by long use of belladonna.","pos":""}],"ATROPOUS":[{"def":"Not inverted; orthotropous.","pos":""}],"ATROUS":[{"def":"Coal-black; very black.","pos":""}],"ATRYPA":[{"def":"A extinct genus of Branchiopoda, very common in Silurian limestones.","pos":""}]}